Package gameobjects.staticobjects

Class Poop

java.lang.Object
gameobjects.GameObject
gameobjects.staticobjects.StaticObject
gameobjects.staticobjects.DestroyableStaticObject
gameobjects.staticobjects.Poop
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Poop
extends DestroyableStaticObject
A Poop is a DestroyableStaticObject, that can both be destroyed by Tears and Bombs.

To check what the variable from Poop are please refer to StaticObject and GameObject.

  • Constructor Details

    • Poop

      public Poop​(int posx, int posy, Room room)
      Constructs a new Poop, whose room is specified by the Room argument. The position is calculated using the Tiles size and the posx and posy argument.
      Parameters:
      posx - the position on the x axes
      posy - the position on the y axes
      room - the room the Poop will be in
